{"_type":"memory","key":"macos-git-hook-gotcha-gnu-timeout-is-not","value":"macOS git-hook gotcha: GNU 'timeout' is NOT installed on this machine, so the beads pre-commit/pre-push hooks run 'bd hooks run' WITHOUT a timeout guard. If multiple bd processes contend for the Dolt lock (e.g. bd init's own commit colliding with manual git commits), the hook hangs INDEFINITELY and git commit/push silently stalls. Fix when it happens: kill the stuck 'bd hooks run' + 'bd export' processes (ps aux | grep bd) to clear the lock, then retry — a single serialized commit works fine. Permanent fix: brew install coreutils and put its gnubin on PATH so 'timeout' exists."}
